<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Psalms 13:1-6</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="150">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="6">
<p class="w">To&nbsp;the&nbsp;director. A&nbsp;melody&nbsp;of&nbsp;David.
</p><p class="l"><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">How long, O Jehovah, will you forget me? Forever?<br><span class="z">How long will you conceal your face from me?</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">How long shall I set resistance in my soul,<br><span class="z">Grief in my heart by day?</span><br><span class="z">How long will my enemy be exalted over me?</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">Do look [upon me]; answer me, O Jehovah my God.<br><span class="z">Do make my eyes shine, that I may not fall asleep in death,</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">That my enemy may not say: “I have won out over him!”<br><span class="z">[That] my adversaries themselves may [not] be joyful because I am made to stagger.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">As for me, in your loving-kindness I have trusted;<br><span class="z">Let my heart be joyful in your salvation.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">I will sing to Jehovah, for he has dealt rewardingly with me.</span>
</p>
</form>

