<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Psalms 23:1-6</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="150">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="6">
<p class="w">A melody of David.
</p><p class="l"><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Jehovah is my Shepherd.<br><span class="z">I shall lack nothing.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">In grassy pastures he makes me lie down;<br><span class="z">By well-watered resting-places he conducts me.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">My soul he refreshes.<br><span class="z">He leads me in the tracks of righteousness for his name’s sake.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Even though I walk in the valley of deep shadow,<br><span class="z">I fear nothing bad,</span><br><span class="p">For you are with me;</span><br><span class="z">Your rod and your staff are the things that comfort me.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">You arrange before me a table in front of those showing hostility to me.<br><span class="z">With oil you have greased my head;</span><br><span class="z">My cup is well filled.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">Surely goodness and loving-kindness themselves will pursue me all the days of my life;<br><span class="z">And I will dwell in the house of Jehovah to the length of days. </span></span>
</p>
</form>

