<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Psalms 60:1-12</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="150">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="12">
<p class="w">To the director on The Lily of Reminder. Mik&acute;tam. Of David. For teaching. When he engaged in a struggle with A&acute;ram-na&middot;ha&middot;ra&acute;im and A&acute;ram-Zo&acute;bah, and Jo&acute;ab proceeded to return and strike down E&acute;dom in the Valley of Salt, even twelve thousand.
</p><p class="l"><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">O God, you have cast us off, you have broken through us,<br><span class="z">You have become incensed. You should restore us.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">You have caused the earth to rock, you have split it open.<br><span class="z">Heal its breaches, for it has tottered.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">You have caused your people to see hardship.<br><span class="z">You have made us drink wine sending us reeling.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">You have given to those fearing you a signal<br><span class="z">To flee zigzag on account of the bow. <i>Se&acute;lah.</i></span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">In order that your beloved ones may be rescued,<br><span class="z">O do save with your right hand and answer us.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">God himself has spoken in his holiness:<br><span class="z">“I will exult, I will give out She&acute;chem as a portion;</span><br><span class="z">And the low plain of Suc&acute;coth I shall measure off.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">Gil&acute;e&middot;ad belongs to me and Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh belongs to me,<br><span class="z">And E&acute;phra&middot;im is the fortress of my head one;</span><br><span class="z">Judah is my commander’s staff.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">Mo&acute;ab is my washing pot.<br><span class="z">Over E&acute;dom I shall throw my sandal.</span><br><span class="z">Over Phi&middot;lis&acute;ti&middot;a I shall shout in triumph.”</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">Who will bring me to the besieged city?<br><span class="z">Who will certainly lead me as far as E&acute;dom?</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Is it not you, O God, who have cast us off<br><span class="z">And who do not go forth with our armies as God?</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">Do give us assistance from distress,<br><span class="z">As salvation by earthling man is worthless.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">By God we shall gain vital energy,<br><span class="z">And he himself will tread down our adversaries. </span></span>
</p>
</form>

