<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Psalms 67:1-7</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="150">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="7">
<p class="w">To the director on stringed instruments. A melody, a song.
</p><p class="l"><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">God himself will show us favor and bless us;<br><span class="z">He will make his face shine upon us—<i>Se&acute;lah</i>—</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">That your way may be known in the earth,<br><span class="z">Your salvation even among all the nations.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">Let peoples laud you, O God;<br><span class="z">Let the peoples, all of them, laud you.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Let national groups rejoice and cry out joyfully,<br><span class="z">For you will judge the peoples with uprightness;</span><br><span class="z">And as for national groups, on the earth you will lead them. <i>Se&acute;lah.</i></span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">Let peoples laud you, O God;<br><span class="z">Let peoples, all of them, laud you.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">The earth itself will certainly give its produce;<br><span class="z">God, our God, will bless us.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">God will bless us,<br><span class="z">And all the ends of the earth will fear him. </span></span>
</p>
</form>

