<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Psalms 93:1-5</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="150">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="5">
<p class="l"><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Jehovah himself has become king!<br><span class="z">With eminence he is clothed;</span><br><span class="p">Jehovah is clothed—with strength he has girded himself.</span><br><span class="z">The productive land also becomes firmly established so that it cannot be made to totter.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">Your throne is firmly established from long ago;<br><span class="z">You are from time indefinite.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">The rivers have raised, O Jehovah,<br><span class="z">The rivers have raised their sound;</span><br><span class="z">The rivers keep raising their pounding.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Above the sounds of vast waters, the majestic breaking waves of the sea,<br><span class="z">Jehovah is majestic in the height.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">Your own reminders have proved very trustworthy.<br><span class="z">Holiness is befitting to your own house, O Jehovah, for length of days. </span></span>
</p>
</form>

