<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Psalms 127:1-5</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="150">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="5">
<p class="w">A&nbsp;Song&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;Ascents. Of&nbsp;Solomon.
</p><p class="l"><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Unless Jehovah himself builds the house,<br><span class="z">It is to no avail that its builders have worked hard on it.</span><br><span class="z">Unless Jehovah himself guards the city,</span><br><span class="z">It is to no avail that the guard has kept awake.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">To no avail it is for <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> men that <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> are rising up early,<br><span class="z">That <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> are sitting down late,</span><br><span class="p">That <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> are eating food with pains.</span><br><span class="z">Just like this he gives sleep even to his beloved one.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">Look! Sons are an inheritance from Jehovah;<br><span class="z">The fruitage of the belly is a reward.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Like arrows in the hand of a mighty man,<br><span class="z">So are the sons of youth.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">Happy is the able-bodied man that has filled his quiver with them.<br><span class="z">They will not be ashamed,</span><br><span class="z">For they will speak with enemies in the gate. </span></span>
</p>
</form>

