<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Psalms 128:1-6</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="150">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="6">
<p class="w">A Song of the Ascents.
</p><p class="l"><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Happy is everyone fearing Jehovah,<br><span class="z">Who is walking in his ways.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">For you will eat the toil of your own hands.<br><span class="z">Happy you will be and it will be well with you.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">Your wife will be like a fruit-bearing vine<br><span class="z">In the innermost parts of your house.</span><br><span class="z">Your sons will be like slips of olive trees all around your table.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Look! That is how the able-bodied man will be blessed<br><span class="z">Who fears Jehovah.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">Jehovah will bless you out of Zion.<br><span class="z">See also the good of Jerusalem all the days of your life,</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">And see the sons of your sons.<br><span class="z">May there be peace upon Israel. </span></span>
</p>
</form>

